# Day 3 - Salesforce Data Modeling

## 1. Difference Between App, Object, Record, and Field

| Term | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| App | A collection of related objects, tabs, and features |
| Object | Database table that stores data |
| Record | A single row of data inside an object |
| Field | Individual information stored in an object |

### Example:

College Management App

Student Object

Record:
Student Name: John

Fields:
- Student ID
- Name
- Email
- Age

---

## 2. Standard vs Custom Objects

### Standard Objects
Pre-built Salesforce objects provided by Salesforce.

Examples:

- Account
- Contact
- Opportunity

### Custom Objects
Objects created by developers according to business needs.

Examples:

- Student
- Faculty
- Course
- Department

---

